definitions.definition: Describing a temperature scale originally defined as having 0°F as the lowest temperature obtainable with a mixture of ice and salt , and 96°F as the temperature of the human body , and now defined with 32°F equal to 0°C, and each degree Fahrenheit equal to 5/9 of a degree Celsius or 5/9 kelvin.

main_definition: Describing a temperature scale originally defined as having 0°F as the lowest temperature obtainable with a mixture of ice and salt , and 96°F as the temperature of the human body , and now defined with 32°F equal to 0°C, and each degree Fahrenheit equal to 5/9 of a degree Celsius or 5/9 kelvin.
